Inside I cheer, because this is for me personally much better, than for example Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who has probably gained a hundred kilos lately (well, that's a bit exaggerated), or the young Selena Gomez.
We should cut out the garments from magazines or search the internet, print them out and then graphically edit them.
The "moodboard", as the whole result is called, should then express our very personal style and our relationship to graphic design.
It is very important to also think about the graphic side of styling.
The stylist not only attracts the models purely physically, but also designs the so-called product page in the journals (according to specific specifications, for example, trend handbags, coats, etc.).
That’s what stylist and designer Mario Kameník told us about.
But that's not until Sunday.
This means that a stylist must have a good overall overview.
The Saturday lecture, filled with information about figure types, was immediately spiced up by three visitors from the industry:
by stylist Jan Pokorn<0xC3><0xBD>, by fashion designer Jakub Polanka and by fashion photographer Ben Ren<0xC4><0x8D>.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and that a stylist should be able to take advantage of it.
And a sent-in stylist can work with a single piece of clothing in very different ways.
The magic word is variability.
For example, you can wear a trench coat as usual over the jeans, such as a t-shirt or coat, but you can also wear it on the naked body, wear heel shoes and wear it as a dress.
It is enough to roll up the sleeves or the collar and the whole look looks quite different.
"Play with it," he stressed.
But most of all, the advice was: "First you need to know the rules perfectly."
"Only then can you hurt her," Jakub said.
Finally, I realize why we have to pause all these teachings, what you can combine with what and why, even if you often see something completely different in fashion journals.
Not to mention fashion shows.
Thanks to the photographer Ben, I now know that a stylist must have prepared a lot more clothing variants than he ultimately photographs.
So for a fashion story with ten pages (to say ten outfits) you have to be prepared to style at least fifteen.
And also that the clothing on the photo in combination with other accessories sometimes looks quite different than in reality.
All of this is to be expected in the design of the outfit.
That image and style sometimes make up half of the success, that was also confirmed by Jan Pokorn<0xC3><0xBD>.
All you have to do is look at Madonna, a not-so-brilliant singer whose image and marketing have turned into a world star.
