Observe the attitude, laughter, voice quality of your subject.
You should know better when someone is usually constantly tripping with their foot, so they don’t wrongly accuse him of tripping with his foot during a meeting.
Then pay attention to accumulations of conspicuous verbal and nonverbal behaviors.
