The court approves the transition to digital television in Mexico for 2015
The transition from analog to digital signals has been one of the most important changes in recent years worldwide.
The Supreme Court of Mexico (SCJN) dismissed the constitutional lawsuits filed by the Senate and the House of Representatives against the presidential decree requiring the shift from analog to digital signals from 2021 to 2015 due to the lack of eight votes required to challenge the law.
