In favour of the project, only Zaldívar, Jorge Mario Pardo, Margarita Luna and Sánchez Cordero voted themselves.
With this argument, both the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies filed constitutional complaints against the Decree-Law. After accepting the complaints, Minister Sánchez Cordero no longer applied the Decree-Law and stopped all activities to establish the digital transmission.
