In addition, the total counting of the fully filled ballots may take place if there is a difference between the alleged winner and the second-placed person equal to or less than one percent, provided that at the beginning of the meeting an explicit request is made by the party or coalition chairman, who is the second of the aforementioned candidates.
The counting of votes may also take place in its entirety if, after completion of the ordinary calculation, it is determined that the difference between the alleged winner and the candidate in second place is equal to or less than one percent, provided that an explicit request is made by a representative of the party whose candidate has become second, in which case the electoral packages subject to partial counting would be excluded.
