At 3:30 p.m., police approached Montral No. 35 after receiving a call from a neighbor who had watched four people attempt to enter the building.
The four were immediately arrested.
Park or mountain?
Apart from the disputes over the fees, the architects agree with the tender.
The municipal call for proposals for the 16 gates reopens the debate on the importance of Collserola in Barcelona.
In the mid-1980s, at the height of the disappearance of the Corporación Metropolitana de Barcelona (CMB), this administration published its blasphemy paper on the promotion of Collserola.
The brochure described the mountain as a huge park in Barcelona city.
It was even compared in numbers to the Central Park of New York.
With the collapse of the CMB in 1987, the park became, in the eyes of many, the upper limit of Barcelona, because the capital of Catalonia is one of the few that does not spread north-south, but up (mountain) and down (sea).
Collserola’s classification as a natural park plays with this idea.
The model was no longer Central Park, but Yellowstone with wild boars in the role of the Yogi bear.
In September, the city issued a giant tender consisting of 16 competitions for further access gates to Collserola.
Without a doubt, a gate points to the concept of a park.
Either this is the case, or someone intends to set gates to the country.
The question arises: Collserola, park or mountain?
Not only from an organizational point of view, but also with a view to a reflection on the city, the tender is the topic of conversation in the mouth of all architects from Barcelona.
It’s almost a recurring topic that two members of this old-fashioned caste who meet in the elevator can resort to.
And this is precisely the fact that provides the fabric for one of the rare similarities between what three architects from Barcelona think about it, and some university professors who have applied for the project.
Miguel Roldán, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayona: The tender is appropriate.
For Roldán "it is necessary to speak about the "front of the mountains" after the attack on the coast, as far as the discourse of Ildefons Cerda, who spoke about the green apples, has not been carried out.
“One should assume that Barcelona’s biggest park is the beach.
Partly because it is easily accessible.
Collserola is more complex,” judges the architect, for whom the title “Gates of Collserola” carries a “lexical trap”: it is not to be imagined “as access to a park, but as a confinement of areas where action must be taken.”
Modol, like Roldán and Bayona with urban development experience, regards the proposal as an “intellectual challenge” that carries “some dangers”.
Dangers due to the "uncertainty that the design of a public space entails today" according to the experience of the 1980s, which had its "swan song" in the area of the Forum.
The first fear is one’s own constraints on what can be built.
"Limiting something always means defining the next step," i.e. going beyond it.
"One has to think about new urban planning tools, because the current [referring to the Plan General Metropolitano (PGM) ] can lead to a real disaster."
Modol, who adheres more closely to the question, simplifies the view that the side of Collserola, which goes towards Vallesana, "can be understood as a park that does not go towards Barcelona", for purely topographical reasons.
Modol recalls that there is already a study by the Patronat de Collserola, which should not "get deaf ears", although he is grateful to the city administration for giving his board the opportunity to participate in this project "from the first moment".
In addition, he notes that the proximity of the mountain to the city is the guideline that allows architects to participate in the debate, although he expresses his "doubts" about whether this technical profile should guide the created multidisciplinary teams ("exactly the right thing," he says) "We architects should be just a tool."
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question in the headline of this article is complex, as there is no global view of Collserola in the tender terms: "There were 16 competitions in cross-section," he says, "on the Axis Mountain-Sea. But there is no longitudinal perspective that looks at the area as a whole."
This, at least in his case, led him to participate in the 16 competitions.
Otherwise, the program and the definition of a project for a gate would collide with that of the architect of the gate next to it.
In his opinion, the city should absolutely guarantee that the strip directly above the Ronda de Dalt is equipped in its entire length to create a smooth transition between the city and green areas.
Casino forgives Jonás Larrazábal who comes free
After 72 days of silence, Casino Red’s authorized representative released the brother of the Mayor of Monterrey from the trial that is being held against him for alleged blackmail.
After 72 days of imprisonment, Manuel Jonás Larrazábal is released after the authorized representative of Casino Red has forgiven him before the District’s Second Criminal Court, which is leading the trial against the brother of the Mayor of Monterrey for extortion.
After the assassination of Casino Royale, Sergio Gil García, the owner of Casino Red, released a series of photos and videos showing Manuel Jonás, who allegedly forced him to pay a sum of money for the city council to approve the secret operation of the betting house.
