The only difference is the degree of generosity.
The fear of the invasion of the national soil by hordes of Polish plumbers was shared in 2005 by both the right and the left.
The immigrants were perceived by both camps as a burden for the economy and French society.
The only difference is the degree of generosity that one is willing to admit to immigrants.
In his program, François Hollande confines himself to banalities that indicate that partnership development allows us to solve our "migration problems".
